<DOC><DOCNO> AP880724-0075 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-24-88 2221EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-China-Storm     07-24 0176</FIRST><SECOND>AM-China-Storm,0182</SECOND><HEAD>Hailstorm, Flooding Kill 54 in China</HEAD><DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Heavy rains accompanied by hail flooded wideareas of northwestern China, collapsing thousands of homes andkilling 54 people, an official report said Sunday.   The storm was the latest in a series of weather disasters inChina that have claimed nearly 600 lives in the past week.   Up to 5.6 inches of rain fell in just over two hours Saturday inthree counties of Gansu province, the Xinhua News Agency said.   It reported that large areas of farmland were flooded andthousands of mud houses and cave homes, typical to the region,collapsed.   The brief report did not say if the reported victims were killedby the collapsing homes.   In Xifeng City, one of the hardest-hit areas, 730 homescollapsed and shops and warehouses were flooded, Xinhua said.   Twenty deaths were reported from Typhoon Warren, which sweptinto southeastern Guangdong province on Tuesday with winds of up to80 mph.   Meanwhile, a drought and heat wave in central China have claimednearly 500 lives.</TEXT></DOC>